column1: #Text=Grover Beach is in San Luis Obispo County in the Central Coast region of California .
#Text=It is part of the Five Cities Metropolitan Area which also includes Oceano to the south , Arroyo Grande to the east , and Pismo Beach and Shell Beach to the north .
#Text=Grover Beach is also the southern terminus of Highway 227 .
#Text=Highway 101 is a major freeway that goes near Grover Beach .
#Text=On the 101 , you can go south to Santa Maria , Santa Barbara , and eventually to Los Angeles , and north to San Luis Obispo , Salinas , and eventually to San Francisco .
#Text=On the 1 , you could go south to Guadalupe and Lompoc , while you could go north to nearby Pismo Beach to meet the 101 .
#Text=The 227 goes north to San Luis Obispo .
#Text=The nearest airport with commercial flights is San Luis Obispo Airport , approximately 10 miles north of Grover Beach .
#Text=Scheduled flights are available to Los Angeles and San Francisco on United Express 's Skywest Airlines , and Phoenix on American Eagle .
#Text=Oceano County Airport is located just south of Grover Beach and it is used mostly for general aviation .

#Text=Amtrak serves Grover Beach via its Pacific Surfliner train between San Luis Obispo and San Diego , there are two daily departures in each direction and several additional Amtrak Thruway buses connecting with trains in Santa Barbara . is located at 180 W Grand Ave.
#Text=SLO South County Transit provides bus service in Grover Beach , Oceano , Pismo Beach and Shell Beach .
#Text=The main transit hub is at Ramona Garden Park at 9th Street and Ramona Ave.
#Text=Go to Pismo State Beach , where vehicles are permitted on the beach , by traveling west on Grand Avenue from Highway 1 .
#Text=Fatte 's Pizza of Grover Beach , 1741 W Grand Ave , ☏ +1805 489-5555 .

#Text=Pismo Beach - Grover Beach 's neighbor to the north is a tourism-focused coastal town that has more than 65 restaurants and 30 lodging options , and draws visitors with its beautiful coastline , annual clam festival , and the thousands of monarch butterflies that gather to spend the winter in a grove at the edge of town .
